tafsir[4]{c,v,t}:
  15,4,"(And We destroyed no township) We destroyed no people of a township (but there was a known decree for it) except that there is an appointed term for their destruction."
  15,5,"(No nation can outstrip its term) He says: no nation perishes or is destroyed before the appointed time for its perishing or destruction (nor can they lag behind) no nation is given respite when its appointed time comes."
  15,11,"(And never came there unto them a messenger) who was sent to them (but they did mock him) but they did deride the messenger."
  15,12,"(Thus do We make it) We leave denial (traverse the hearts of the guilty) the hearts of the idolaters:"